## 3. Non-Functional Requirements

<!--
  NFRs constrain how the system behaves across all use cases.
  State explicit thresholds — no vague statements ("should be fast", "must be secure").
  Every NFR must be traceable to a PROJECT.md constraint or success metric.
-->

### Performance

**NFR-P-01:** [Specific latency target] — e.g., "CLI commands (excluding network calls) complete within [N]ms at p95 under normal load."

**NFR-P-02:** [Specific throughput or startup requirement] — e.g., "CLI startup time from invocation to first output is under [N]ms on [target hardware baseline]."

<!-- Add NFR-P-NN for each distinct performance requirement. -->

**Traces to:** PROJECT.md Constraint: [constraint text]

---

### Security

**NFR-S-01:** [Authentication requirement] — e.g., "All commands that read or write project data require an authenticated session. Unauthenticated commands exit with code [N] and output [specific message]."

**NFR-S-02:** [Data handling requirement] — e.g., "API tokens are stored in [location] with [access controls]. Tokens are never written to stdout, log files, or error output."

**NFR-S-03:** [Authorization requirement] — e.g., "Users can only read and write time entries they created. Attempting to modify another user's entry returns [specific error]."

<!-- Add NFR-S-NN for each distinct security requirement. -->

**Traces to:** PROJECT.md Constraint: [constraint text]

---

### Reliability

**NFR-R-01:** [Error rate target] — e.g., "Sync operations succeed for [N]% of attempts when the external API is available and responding within its documented SLA."

**NFR-R-02:** [Degraded-mode behavior] — e.g., "When [external dependency] is unavailable, [what the system does — stores locally, retries with backoff, etc.] without data loss."

**NFR-R-03:** [Recovery requirement] — e.g., "No locally stored time entry is lost due to a CLI crash, SIGTERM, or SIGKILL."

**Traces to:** PROJECT.md Constraint: [constraint text]

---

### Observability

**NFR-O-01:** [Logging requirement] — e.g., "All sync operations log: timestamp, number of entries attempted, number succeeded, number failed, and any error messages — written to [location]."

**NFR-O-02:** [Error output requirement] — e.g., "All user-facing errors include: a plain-language description, the specific cause (where determinable), and the remediation action."

**NFR-O-03:** [Diagnostic requirement] — e.g., "A user experiencing a sync failure can identify whether the failure is due to authentication, network, or API error without reading source code."

